{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17413336","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17413336"},"attributes":{"position":15,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T08:07:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T08:07:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2033"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17503461","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17503461"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:01:17+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:01:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2033"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261100"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:52:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T10:28:52+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":62,"questionsAnswered":61,"marksTotal":61,"marksAttainable":61,"marksAttempted":61,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T09:15:31+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0.2,"questionsCorrect":12,"marksCorrect":12},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"2033","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2033"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.77,0.11,0.02,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2033"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"98509"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2033","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2033"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2033"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80938"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"3340"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4971"},{"type":"tags","id":"11632"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"4888"},{"type":"contributions","id":"4889"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33781"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42436"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"98509","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/98509"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 31-year-old man is brought into the Emergency Department presenting with worsening confusion for the past 3 days. The paramedics elaborated that the patient has a background of bipolar disorder with psychotic features for which he is on long-standing lithium therapy. His psychotic symptoms became worse 2 weeks ago and he has since been started on quetiapine. He does not smoke cigarettes or take illicit drugs, however, consumes 1-2 standard drinks of beer each day.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUpon examination, he appears diaphoretic and disoriented with incoherent speech. His vital signs are as follows:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETemperature 39.4\u003Csup\u003Eo\u003C/sup\u003EC\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHeart rate 130/min\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBlood pressure 170/110mmHg\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERespiratory rate 12/min\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHe has generalised muscle rigidity with deep tendon reflexes of 1+ bilaterally. Abdomen is soft and nontender. Lung sounds are clear. Full blood count results appear normal. Creatinine kinase is over 1000 U/L (RR: 22 \u2013 198 U/L).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Serotonin syndrome","Neuroleptic malignant syndrome","Lithium toxicity","Delirium tremens","Bacterial meningitis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENeuroleptic malignant syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E (NMS) is a condition associated with antipsychotic drugs, commonly used in schizophrenia and bipolar disorder. Symptoms can include high fever (often above 39.0\u003Csup\u003Eo\u003C/sup\u003EC), autonomic disturbances (i.e. diaphoresis and tachycardia), muscle rigidity and altered mental state. A disproportionately high creatine kinase is often seen in NMS, caused by increased muscle activity. These symptoms normally occur 2 weeks after the first dose. The key aspect of management is the discontinuation of the antipsychotic drug.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerotonin syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E presents similarly to NMS, with symptoms such as fever, altered mental state and diaphoresis. However, the differentiating factor between serotonin syndrome and NMS is the duration of symptoms \u2013 serotonin syndrome occurs more acutely, commonly within 24-48 hours, whereas NMS occurs 2 weeks after the first dose of antipsychotic. Similarly, the neuromuscular symptoms seen in serotonin syndrome consist of hyperreflexia rather than hyporeflexia seen in this particular patient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELithium toxicity\u003C/strong\u003E can cause delirium and neuromuscular symptoms such as muscle fasciculation and tremor. However, this patient presented with fever, hypertension and elevated creatinine kinase. These are not seen in lithium toxicity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelirium tremens\u003C/strong\u003E, a condition caused by alcohol withdrawal, may lead to altered mental state associated with fever and hypertension. However, this diagnosis is less likely because this patient drinks only 1-2 standard drinks per day.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBacterial meningitis\u003C/strong\u003E could cause fever and altered mental state. However, this patient has a normal full blood count, including a normal white cell count. This would be raised with a bacterial infection. Similarly, bacterial meningitis does not explain an elevated creatine kinase, autonomic dysfunction and rigidity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Neuroleptic malignant syndrome is a rare complication of all antipsychotic drugs."],"references":["Velamoor V, Norman R, Caroff S, Mann S, Sullivan K, Antelo R. Progression of Symptoms in Neuroleptic Malignant Syndrome. The Journal of Nervous and Mental Disease. 1994;182(3):168-173.","Neuroleptic malignant syndrome. American Journal of Psychiatry. 1985;142(10):1137-1145.","Bodner R, Lynch T, Lewis L, Kahn D. Serotonin syndrome. Neurology. 1995;45(2):219-223.","Meltzer, H. Antipsychotic Agents \u0026 Lithium. In: Basic and Clinical Pharmacology, 11th ed, McGraw Hill, New York 2009. p.487."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80938"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2033"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80938","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/80938"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-14T13:43:24+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-14T13:44:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2033"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"98509"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10